íŸ@cead978624082d751e2ef7cafb9cd846e879dbb2a2e1e881dbe64e0965932275⁄ŸTitle: title: into filesize
Path: Examples
Content:
Convert string to filesize in table.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> [[device size]; ["/dev/sda1" "200"] ["/dev/loop0" "50"]] | into filesize size
‚ï≠‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ïÆ
‚îÇ # ‚îÇ   device   ‚îÇ size  ‚îÇ
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îº‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îº‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î§
‚îÇ 0 ‚îÇ /dev/sda1  ‚îÇ 200 B ‚îÇ
‚îÇ 1 ‚îÇ /dev/loop0 ‚îÇ  50 B ‚îÇ
‚ï∞‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¥‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¥‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ïØ


```
Convert string to filesize.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> '2' | into filesize
2 B

```
Convert float to filesize.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 8.3 | into filesize
8 B

```
Convert int to filesize.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 5 | into filesize
5 B

```
Convert file size to filesize.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 4KB | into filesize
4.0 kB

```
Convert string with unit to filesize.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> '-1KB' | into filesize
-1.0 kB

```
